                        "content": "A client with hiatal hernia chronically experiences heartburn following meals. The nurse would plan to teach the client to avoid which action because it is contraindicated with a hiatal hernia?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHiatal hernia is caused by a protrusion of a portion of the stomach above the diaphragm where the esophagus usually is positioned. The client usually experiences pain from reflux caused by ingestion of irritating foods, lying flat following meals or at night, and eating large or fatty meals. Relief is obtained with the intake of small, frequent, and bland meals; use of H2-receptor antagonists and antacids; and elevation of the thorax following meals and during sleep.",
                        "id": "3ab3896a17c84394b1920e9a98abc25d",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "723910ca820f4cdf868238f2b5870060",
                                "content": "Esophagitis"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c48e89b2a2b241839346593d834da646",
                                "content": "Hiatal hernia"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
