                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHiatal hernias occur when the upper portion of the stomach protrudes through the diaphragm. The pressure created by this process can result in acid reflux. Eliminate options 1 because although esophagitis is a complication of hiatal hernia, there are no data in the question to indicate that the esophagus is inflamed. Next, eliminate option 3 because an umbilical hernia refers to a protrusion of abdominal contents through a weakened spot in the abdominal wall near the navel area. Eliminate option 4 because if a stricture was present then it would be unlikely that protrusion would occur. Therefore, option 2 is the correct answer.",
                        "id": "476bb30b31344d5eae96557e98d87324",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "cb7b2087f5fe45e4ae4bc5a6769686e9",
                                "content": "Offer the client small, frequent meals"
                            },
                            {
