                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client diagnosed with a hiatal hernia. Which priority nursing action would the nurse include in the care plan for this client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHiatal hernias occur when the upper portion of the stomach protrudes through the diaphragm. Common complications of hiatal hernia include gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), esophagitis, hemorrhage from gastric erosion, esophageal narrowing, stomach ulcerations, hernia strangulation, and regurgitation with subsequent tracheal aspiration. Although options 1, 3, and 4 are important measures to take while caring for a client with a hiatal hernia, option 2 is the priority action, as the client is at risk for tracheal aspiration and would remain in an upright position to prevent this complication and protect the airway.",
                        "id": "c9ec4f53a26548dba30abe40e6babe3a",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9da02859c89c452f81ea85919aa73e92",
                                "content": "Removal of the herniated gastric sac"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "63b3f4e81cc24d69b7f06b45112450d0",
                                "content": "Closure of the hiatal defect in the diaphragm"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "5254859fb55a4a35ad73d697bebd2722",
                                "content": "The upper portion of the stomach is attached below the diaphragm."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "4222d99710e54297a8fc639a0f9d03a2",
                                "content": "The fundus of the stomach is wrapped around the distal portion of the esophagus and sutured together."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "9da02859c89c452f81ea85919aa73e92",
                                    "content": "Removal of the herniated gastric sac"
                                },
