                        "content": "The client diagnosed with bilateral inguinal hernias requiring surgical repair asks the nurse to describe the condition. The nurse plans to make which appropriate nursing response?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThere are several types of hernias, including hiatal hernia, umbilical hernia, femoral hernia, inguinal hernia, and incisional or ventral hernia. Each differs based on the anatomical location of the hernia. Eliminate option 1 first, as this describes an umbilical hernia. Next, eliminate option 3, as this describes an incisional or ventral hernia. Eliminate option 4, as this describes a femoral hernia. Inguinal hernias are more common and occur when abdominal contents protrude through weakened abdominal muscles near the spermatic cord in in those with a penis or the round ligament in those with a vagina. Therefore, option 2 is correct.",
                        "id": "eef2e734f31c4458bf2410a11a008fe3",
                        "mark": "0",
